data.text: Elizabeth Jennings, 69, was born in San Antonio, TX to Roy Dossey and Artie May on August 13, 1951. Loving wife, mother, grandmother passed away on Thursday, November 26, 2020 in Hobbs, NM. Elizabeth was a graduate of Hobbs High School, Class of 1969 and attended NMJC. She was an administrator for Key Energy Services. When she was not doing secretarial work, she loved spending it with her family fishing or reading romance novels. Elizabeth was predeceased by her parents, and two grandchildren Casie Jennings and Kelly Faith. Left to cherish her memory is her husband of 49 years, David Jennings; sons, Casey and Chris Jennings (Kelly) and daughter, Jennifer Williams (Shane); granddaughters: Mariah, Katie & Katelynn Jennings, Taylor & Chandler Jennings and Mackenzie Hand, Kana, Bree & Peyton Williams; and great grandchild Karter Hall. A Memorial Service will be held at a later date.
